1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:19,513
CaseFlow is an agentic alert-resolution workspace for GoTyme's 
anti-money-laundering and know-your-transaction analysts. It begins where 
monitoring ends: at an alert. All data shown is synthetic. This case has an 
incomplete Travel Rule payload, and the analyst's goal is explicit. Reach a 
defensible next action, not blindly trust the vendor score.

2
00:00:19,513 --> 00:00:41,570
When the analyst runs CaseFlow, a live language model agent plans, then calls 
tools. It fetches the customer profile, the transaction, wallet intelligence, 
and the Travel Rule payload, and it searches the versioned policy corpus. 
Each tool call carries real arguments, and every step becomes a timestamped, 
SHA-256 hashed audit event. Nothing is fabricated.

3
00:00:41,570 --> 00:01:04,634
A second language model role, the Compliance Challenger, adversarially 
reviews the decision. Here, beneficiary identity and beneficiary VASP are 
missing. Under clause TR-1.2 the evidence is incomplete, so CaseFlow returns 
request evidence and names exactly what is missing. A deterministic guardrail 
guarantees an incomplete Travel Rule payload can never be sealed as clear or 
escalate.

4
00:01:04,634 --> 00:01:31,341
The analyst adds the seeded beneficiary payload and resumes the same case. No 
audit trail is lost. The agent re-investigates with the now complete 
evidence. A residency contradiction remains, so under clause KYC-2.4 it now 
recommends escalate, with calibrated confidence, cited clauses, evidence 
identifiers, and an analyst-ready narrative. It is still a recommendation. 
The analyst accepts, overrides with a reason, or requests more evidence.

5
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:49,746
Nothing here is asserted. Running the real agent over twenty labelled 
synthetic cases, CaseFlow measured ninety percent disposition agreement, one 
hundred percent policy citation recall, and one hundred percent 
request-evidence recall, with zero fabricated packets. The labels live 
outside the runtime prompts, and misses are reported honestly.

6
00:01:49,746 --> 00:02:08,721
This is CaseFlow's core idea. Non-deterministic reasoning inside 
deterministic governance. The model plans, investigates, and argues, while 
typed contracts, round limits, and hard evidence gates decide what can be 
sealed. And learning stays human gated. Analyst feedback drafts a versioned 
policy proposal, never a silent change.

